shows taking a hiatus in the upcoming weeks due to extensive coverage of the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 7047, \"to\": 7213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7059, \"end\": 7062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul_Broadcasting_System\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3110474632584194e-66, \"text\": \"SBS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul_Broadcasting_System\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul_Broadcasting_System\"}, {\"begin\": 7078, \"end\": 7086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inkigayo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Inkigayo\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inkigayo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inkigayo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means that fans will not be able to enjoy the popular music program on July 21, July 28, and August 4.\", \"from\": 7214, \"to\": 7321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The network has apologized for any inconvenience and asked for viewers' understanding as they prioritize Olympic coverage, which will dominate from July 24 to August 12.\", \"from\": 7322, \"to\": 7491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This brief hiatus does not stop with Inkigayo.\", \"from\": 7497, \"to\": 7543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7534, \"end\": 7542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inkigayo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Inkigayo\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inkigayo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inkigayo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other major music shows are also being temporarily sidelined.\", \"from\": 7544, \"to\": 7605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Show will not air on July 16, 23, or 30, while M Countdown and Music Bank will skip August 1 and August 2/9, respectively.\", \"from\": 7606, \"to\": 7732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Music Core will take breaks on July 27 and August 3.\", \"from\": 7733, \"to\": 7785, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This wave of cancellations has left K-pop fans disheartened, as the lack of broadcast opportunities means fewer chances for their favorite artists to win the coveted music show awards.\", \"from\": 7787, \"to\": 7971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, fans are left hoping that the networks might find alternative ways to acknowledge achievements and celebrate artist milestones despite the absence of these popular music shows.\", \"from\": 7972, \"to\": 8159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Paris Olympics draws near, the focus will understandably shift, but K-pop fans eagerly await any creative solutions to keep the spirit of music awards alive during this temporary hiatus.\", \"from\": 8161, \"to\": 8354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the SBS Gayo Daejeon Summer is set to light up the midyear with a spectacular showcase of performances from top artists.\", \"from\": 8360, \"to\": 8491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hosting this star-studded event are NCT's Doyoung, IVE's An Yu Jin, and TXT's Yeonjun, each a former Inkigayo MC.\", \"from\": 8492, \"to\": 8605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8534, \"end\": 8541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doyoung_(singer)\", \"score\": 0.9883812584543248, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Doyoung\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doyoung_(singer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doyoung_(singer)\"}, {\"begin\": 8543, \"end\": 8546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_Institute_of_Vocational_Education\", \"score\": 0.9999999999317879, \"rank\": 6.705791623630603e-11, \"text\": \"IVE\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_Institute_of_Vocational_Education\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong_Institute_of_Vocatio